---
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
import Subscribe from '../components/Subscribe.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Services"
    description="Private blockchain consulting, proof-of-concept builds, architecture audits, and managed infrastructure for tamper-proof record-keeping."
    showHeader={false}
>
    <article class="mb-16 sm:mb-24">
        <header class="mb-12">
            <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl leading-tight font-medium sm:text-5xl sm:leading-tight">Services</h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed sm:text-base">
                I help companies build tamper-proof record-keeping and fraud prevention infrastructure. The blockchain is the <em>how</em> — the value is in
                what it makes possible for your business.
            </p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose sm:prose-lg max-w-none">
            <!-- Entry Point -->
            <section class="border-main mb-12 border border-dashed p-6 sm:p-8">
                <h2>Private Chain Proof of Concept — $5,000</h2>
                <p>
                    The fastest way to see if private blockchain fits your use case. In 4 weeks, you get a working system you can demo to stakeholders — not a
                    slide deck.
                </p>

                <h3>What You Get</h3>
                <p><strong>Week 1-2:</strong> Discovery calls + architecture document tailored to your specific use case.</p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Week 3-4:</strong> Working proof-of-concept with a 2-node private blockchain, 1 smart contract, basic web UI, and API documentation.
                </p>

                <h3>Deliverables</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Source code (MIT licensed — it's yours)</li>
                    <li>Docker Compose for one-command deployment</li>
                    <li>Architecture document with production scaling notes</li>
                    <li>Recorded demo walkthrough</li>
                    <li>30-minute follow-up call after delivery</li>
                </ul>

                <p>
                    <strong>Why $5K works:</strong> It's low enough for a CTO to approve without board involvement, but high enough to filter out tire-kickers.
                    Most PoCs lead to full implementation engagements.
                </p>

                <div class="not-prose mt-6">
                    <Button href="/contact">Book a Discovery Call</Button>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Upsell Path -->
            <h2>From PoC to Production</h2>
            <p>The PoC is the starting point. Here's the typical path:</p>

            <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
                <div class="border-main border border-dashed p-4">
                    <p class="font-serif text-lg font-medium">$5K</p>
                    <p class="text-sm">Proof of Concept</p>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-xs opacity-70">4 weeks, working demo</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-main border border-dashed p-4">
                    <p class="font-serif text-lg font-medium">$20-50K</p>
                    <p class="text-sm">Full Implementation</p>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-xs opacity-70">Production deployment, multi-node chain, custom contracts</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-main border border-dashed p-4">
                    <p class="font-serif text-lg font-medium">$2-5K/month</p>
                    <p class="text-sm">Managed Infrastructure</p>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-xs opacity-70">Monitoring, updates, support, uptime SLA</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Additional Services -->
            <h2>Additional Services</h2>

            <h3>Consulting — $500/hour</h3>
            <p>
                For teams that have blockchain expertise but need a second opinion. Architecture reviews, security assessments, performance optimization, or
                just a sounding board for technical decisions.
            </p>

            <h3>Blockchain Architecture Audit — $15,000</h3>
            <p>
                Deep review of an existing blockchain implementation. I examine your smart contracts, node configuration, consensus setup, security model, and
                disaster recovery. You get a detailed report with prioritized recommendations.
            </p>

            <h3>Managed Private Blockchain Infrastructure — $2-5K/month</h3>
            <p>
                I run your private blockchain so your team doesn't have to. Includes monitoring, security patches, node management, backup verification, and
                24-hour response SLA for critical issues.
            </p>

            <!-- Best Fit -->
            <h2>Best Fit</h2>
            <p>My clients are typically:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Real estate title companies</strong> — wire fraud prevention and tamper-proof closing documents</li>
                <li><strong>Legal firms</strong> — M&A, IP transactions, and chain-of-custody for sensitive documents</li>
                <li><strong>Healthcare organizations</strong> — HIPAA-compliant audit trails that can't be backdated</li>
                <li><strong>Government & municipal IT</strong> — transparent public records and accountability systems</li>
                <li><strong>Art & provenance tracking</strong> — verifiable ownership and authentication records</li>
            </ul>

            <p>If your business handles records where tampering would be costly or dangerous, we should talk.</p>

            <div class="not-prose mt-8">
                <Button href="/contact">Start With a Free Discovery Call</Button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>

    <Subscribe class="my-16 sm:my-24" />
</BaseLayout>
